1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:07,200
In the annals of sporting history, few names resonate with the power and reverence of Sachin Ramesh Tendulkar.

2
00:00:07,200 --> 00:00:28,000
Born on April 24, 1973, in Mumbai, India, he would rise from humble beginnings to become a global phenomenon, often hailed as "The Little Master" and "God of Cricket." His journey began remarkably early, making his international debut for India in November 1989 at the tender age of sixteen against formidable opposition.

3
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:31,199
Tendulkar’s arrival heralded a new era in cricket.

4
00:00:31,199 --> 00:00:37,200
A right-handed top-order batsman, his technique was a blend of classical purity and aggressive innovation.

5
00:00:37,200 --> 00:00:43,200
He dominated bowlers across generations, captivating audiences with his fearless stroke play and unwavering concentration.

6
00:00:43,200 --> 00:00:52,400
His career spanned an astonishing twenty-four years, from 1989 to 2013, a testament to his incredible longevity and consistency at the highest level.

7
00:00:52,400 --> 00:01:03,600
From his first Test century against England in 1990 to his first One Day International century in 1994, it was clear that a legend was in the making.

8
00:01:03,600 --> 00:01:09,200
Sachin Tendulkar wasn't just a great player; he was a record-breaker of unparalleled measure.

9
00:01:09,200 --> 00:01:18,000
He holds the record for the most runs in Test cricket, amassing 15,921 runs, and in One Day Internationals with 18,426 runs.

10
00:01:18,000 --> 00:01:25,599
His most iconic achievement remains an unparalleled one hundred international centuries – fifty-one in Tests and forty-nine in ODIs.

11
00:01:25,599 --> 00:01:34,000
He also became the first male cricketer to score an ODI double century, an unbeaten 200 against South Africa in 2010.

12
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:42,799
Having played 200 Tests and 463 ODIs, his presence on the field was almost a constant throughout two decades of international cricket.

13
00:01:42,799 --> 00:01:45,599
Beyond the statistics, Tendulkar was an icon.

14
00:01:45,599 --> 00:01:51,199
For millions in India, he was a symbol of hope, aspiration, and national pride.

15
00:01:51,199 --> 00:02:00,399
His immense popularity transcended cricketing nations, establishing him as one of the most recognized athletes worldwide and a global ambassador for the sport.

16
00:02:00,399 --> 00:02:16,399
His ultimate dream was realized in April 2011, when he was a crucial member of the Indian team that won the ICC Cricket World Cup on home soil, a moment that sparked national jubilation and perfectly capped his incredible journey.

17
00:02:16,399 --> 00:02:21,999
Even after retiring from all forms of international cricket in 2013, Sachin’s influence continues.

18
00:02:21,999 --> 00:02:29,599
He was inducted into the ICC Cricket Hall of Fame in 2019, cementing his place amongst the game's immortals.

19
00:02:29,599 --> 00:02:44,399
His contributions were recognized by the Indian government with the Padma Shri, Padma Vibhushan, and in 2014, the Bharat Ratna – India's highest civilian award, making him its youngest recipient and the first sportsperson to receive it.

20
00:02:44,399 --> 00:02:54,399
Respected for his humble demeanor, sportsmanship, and dedication, Sachin Tendulkar remains a role model, his legacy extending far beyond the boundary ropes, forever inspiring generations.
